text:   President Barack Obama take a bite of a rib as he visits a Kenny's BBQ restaurant in Washington, Wednesday, June 13, 2012. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) U.S. President Barack Obama (R) and Russian Federation President Dmitry Medvedev (L) eat cheeseburgers at Ray's Hell Burger June 24, 2010 in Arlington, Virginia. The two leaders met briefly in the Oval Office earlier and later held a press conference. (Photo by Martin H. Simon-Pool/Getty Images) Democratic presidential candidate U.S. Senator Barack Obama eats a slice of carrot cake during a visit at PJ & Co. Restaurant in Reno, Nevada, on August 17, 2008. (EMMANUEL DUNAND/AFP/Getty Images) U.S. President Barack Obama holds up a hoagie sandwich after holding a roundtable discussion with small business owners at the Taylor Gourmet restaurant in Washington, D.C., May 16, 2012. (SAUL LOEB/AFP/GettyImages) President Barack Obama arrives with pizza at an Organizing for America field office, Sunday, Oct. 14, 2012, in Williamsburg, Va. (AP Photo/Carolyn Kaster) U.S. President Barack Obama eats shaved ice at Tropical Sno in Denison, Iowa, August 13, 2012 during his three-day campaign bus tour through Iowa. (JIM WATSON/AFP/GettyImages) President Barack Obama eats a hot dog while watching in the second half of an NCAA basketball game between Oregon State and Towson in Towson, Md., Saturday, Nov. 26, 2011. (AP Photo/Patrick Semansky) US President Barack Obama cooks steaks on a barbeque during an event on the South Lawn of the White House in Washington, DC, June 19, 2009, for young men from local schools as part of Father's Day festivities.
